title: Bug 110566: Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression for row[0]
description: When setting the filter expression to "row[0] equals to 0", the data set result is incorrect or returns a null result set.
OB: The data set is returning incorrect or null results when an invalid filter expression for row[0] is set.
EB: The data set should return the correct results or an appropriate error message when an invalid filter expression for row[0] is set.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Set the filter expression to "row[0] equals to 0".
2. Retrieve the data set and observe the incorrect or null result.
